1
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:03,090
Then...

2
00:00:03,090 --> 00:00:05,290
can we call today

3
00:00:05,290 --> 00:00:08,410
the first day

4
00:00:08,410 --> 00:00:11,010
of our relationship?

5
00:00:11,820 --> 00:00:13,460
Yes.

6
00:00:17,560 --> 00:00:20,280
- How can I face Aoyama now?
- What should I say to Ichinose?

7
00:00:20,280 --> 00:00:22,060
- No, I...
- No, I...

8
00:00:23,440 --> 00:00:25,200
Well...

9
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,110
go ahead.

10
00:00:29,430 --> 00:00:30,560
I'm sorry.

11
00:00:30,560 --> 00:00:33,610
I'm not actually dating Aoyama.

12
00:00:36,710 --> 00:00:39,180
Me too.

13
00:00:39,180 --> 00:00:41,370
I'm not dating Second Lieutenant Ichinose.

14
00:00:41,370 --> 00:00:43,920
What? It was a lie?

15
00:00:43,920 --> 00:00:44,890
You lied too!

16
00:00:44,890 --> 00:00:48,650
It wasn't a lie! I really was going to, but I couldn't.

17
00:00:48,650 --> 00:00:51,110
You were really going to?

18
00:00:51,110 --> 00:00:52,730
That's worse!

19
00:00:52,730 --> 00:00:55,280
You were the one who told me to!

20
00:00:55,280 --> 00:00:57,430
That's true.

21
00:00:57,430 --> 00:01:00,430
I thought you were going to marry Aoyama.

22
00:01:00,430 --> 00:01:03,440
That's why I agreed to sell this house.

23
00:01:03,440 --> 00:01:07,690
I thought you were dating Ichinose, and that's why I...

24
00:01:08,410 --> 00:01:10,370
That's right.

25
00:01:10,370 --> 00:01:11,700
We

26
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:14,390
sold this house!

27
00:01:14,390 --> 00:01:17,100
Here's the contract.

28
00:01:17,960 --> 00:01:19,670
<i>[Real Estate Sales Contract]</i>

29
00:01:19,670 --> 00:01:23,010
A man named Sachio Yamada bought the house.

30
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:24,750
What is he like?

31
00:01:24,750 --> 00:01:25,790
Well...

32
00:01:25,790 --> 00:01:29,030
Impatient and severe, I guess.

33
00:01:29,030 --> 00:01:30,640
He said he wanted to buy it in cash.

34
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:33,740
Would it be possible to buy it back?

35
00:01:33,740 --> 00:01:36,110
I thought the same thing, so I called him.

36
00:01:36,110 --> 00:01:38,780
I asked if he would reconsider the contract,

37
00:01:38,780 --> 00:01:42,160
then he said it made more sense to discuss it in person.

38
00:01:42,160 --> 00:01:44,430
That's true.

39
00:01:44,430 --> 00:01:47,520
So he said he's coming here now.

40
00:01:47,520 --> 00:01:49,120
- What?
- What?

41
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:56,840
Very suspicious...

42
00:02:02,620 --> 00:02:05,270
Yamada?

43
00:02:05,270 --> 00:02:06,270
Yes.

44
00:02:06,270 --> 00:02:10,320
Thank you for coming out here today.

45
00:02:10,320 --> 00:02:13,540
Um, could you...

46
00:02:13,540 --> 00:02:14,830
I'm very sorry.

47
00:02:14,830 --> 00:02:17,910
Could we talk about this?

48
00:02:17,910 --> 00:02:21,460
You guys are a real pain!

49
00:02:22,090 --> 00:02:24,670
But acting like that

50
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:27,390
is always a blast.

51
00:02:28,010 --> 00:02:30,450
- Mr. Minazuki.
- Minazuki.

52
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:36,320
He was the one who signed this contract.

53
00:02:38,420 --> 00:02:40,520
His name is Sachio Yamada.

54
00:02:40,520 --> 00:02:42,810
Do you know him, Saki?

55
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:47,570
He's the author I've been managing.

56
00:02:47,570 --> 00:02:50,490
The novelist, Ren Minazuki.

57
00:02:50,490 --> 00:02:51,760
Thanks for all that.

58
00:02:51,760 --> 00:02:56,170
Is "Sachio Yamada"

59
00:02:56,170 --> 00:02:59,000
your real name, Minazuki?

60
00:02:59,000 --> 00:03:02,970
I-I don't like how you phrased it... but yes.

61
00:03:02,970 --> 00:03:05,540
I'm shocked!

62
00:03:07,650 --> 00:03:09,680
Sachio Yamada.

63
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:13,710
Why on earth did you buy this place?

64
00:03:14,630 --> 00:03:16,980
Harassment!

65
00:03:17,580 --> 00:03:19,540
Um...

66
00:03:19,540 --> 00:03:21,790
I know it's really selfish,

67
00:03:21,790 --> 00:03:26,610
but could you cancel the contract for this house?

68
00:03:27,330 --> 00:03:28,970
I don't want to.

69
00:03:31,260 --> 00:03:35,080
We've decided to start over.

70
00:03:35,080 --> 00:03:40,140
This house is the first place we lived together, so it's important to us.

71
00:03:40,140 --> 00:03:44,950
If it's possible, we'd like to start over again here.

72
00:03:44,950 --> 00:03:47,490
Samurai b*stard, you're going to live with her again?

73
00:03:47,490 --> 00:03:50,170
It might be difficult on the weekdays,

74
00:03:50,170 --> 00:03:56,000
but I'm hoping to live with her on the weekends, at least.

75
00:03:57,970 --> 00:04:02,530
You guys don't get what's going to happen, do you?

76
00:04:03,370 --> 00:04:05,260
- If you pay me to rent...
- Don't... Don't-

77
00:04:05,260 --> 00:04:08,490
- ...as a landlord...
- Don't touch! Please don't touch it!

78
00:04:08,490 --> 00:04:10,660
...I'll let you keep living here.

79
00:04:10,660 --> 00:04:13,450
How much would we pay in rent?

80
00:04:13,450 --> 00:04:16,560
How does 300,000 a month sound?

81
00:04:16,560 --> 00:04:17,910
Isn't that a little high?

82
00:04:17,910 --> 00:04:20,000
If you don't like it, get out.

83
00:04:24,420 --> 00:04:26,060
What do we do?

84
00:04:28,950 --> 00:04:30,870
I don't know.

85
00:04:30,870 --> 00:04:32,330
Are you guys going to be okay?

86
00:04:32,330 --> 00:04:33,660
I don't know.

87
00:04:33,660 --> 00:04:37,190
You'll get divorced again in no time, huh?

88
00:04:37,190 --> 00:04:40,200
- It's just the first day of our relationship!
- It's just the first day of our relationship!

89
