You seem more energetic than usual.

93
00:04:55,630 --> 00:04:58,860
You can tell? Ouch! I'm okay, I'm okay.

94
00:04:58,860 --> 00:04:59,950
What's with that face?

95
00:04:59,950 --> 00:05:02,190
I knew it! You've got a new girl!

96
00:05:02,190 --> 00:05:07,140
Sort of a new girl, sort of an old girl.

97
00:05:07,140 --> 00:05:08,690
It's your ex-wife?

98
00:05:08,690 --> 00:05:10,210
We've been dating for two days.

99
00:05:10,210 --> 00:05:11,510
- Wow!
- Wow!

100
00:05:11,510 --> 00:05:13,760
- Congratulations!
- Congratulations!

101
00:05:13,760 --> 00:05:15,440
I knew it!

102
00:05:15,440 --> 00:05:17,610
- Let's celebrate.
- No, I don't want any of that!

103
00:05:17,610 --> 00:05:19,210
- Let's get barbeque.
- It's fine!

104
00:05:19,210 --> 00:05:21,600
- Gather up!
- Yes, ma'am!

105
00:05:24,520 --> 00:05:26,620
- Cadet Yasui!
- Yes, ma'am! Cadest Yasui, here!

106
00:05:26,620 --> 00:05:27,970
Begin the JSDF exercises!

107
00:05:27,970 --> 00:05:33,290
- One, two, three, four, five, six...
- One, two, three, four, five, six...

108
00:05:33,290 --> 00:05:35,590
Good morning.

109
00:05:38,590 --> 00:05:41,590
Saki! Did you think about what I said before?

110
00:05:41,590 --> 00:05:44,820
I'm sorry, I haven't decided yet.

111
00:05:44,820 --> 00:05:47,350
You need to think that hard about it?

112
00:05:47,350 --> 00:05:50,000
It's such a good offer!

113
00:05:50,000 --> 00:05:51,150
I'm sorry.

114
00:05:51,150 --> 00:05:54,010
Could you give me a decision by the end of the month?

115
00:05:54,010 --> 00:05:57,550
I have to report to my bosses too, you know.

116
00:05:57,550 --> 00:05:59,580
I understand.

117
00:05:59,580 --> 00:06:03,030
Why are you hesitating about this Pais training?

118
00:06:03,030 --> 00:06:05,860
You've always wanted to go, you were passed over twice,

119
00:06:05,860 --> 00:06:08,100
and you finally got it on the third try!

120
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:11,620
You should definitely go!

121
00:06:11,620 --> 00:06:17,170
Koichi came back, but going to Paris will be a rough sailing.

122
00:06:17,170 --> 00:06:20,550
I want to go to Paris, of course,

123
00:06:20,550 --> 00:06:24,070
but I want to be with Koichi too.

124
00:06:24,070 --> 00:06:27,090
I want kids one day too.

125
00:06:27,090 --> 00:06:29,380
If only it were for one year.

126
00:06:29,380 --> 00:06:31,340
Exactly!

127
00:06:31,340 --> 00:06:36,070
Three years in your 30's is really valuable.

128
00:06:36,070 --> 00:06:39,790
But a chance like this doesn't come along that often.

129
00:06:40,300 --> 00:06:44,580
If I pass up this chance, I don't think I can get assigned to Paris again.

130
00:06:44,580 --> 00:06:47,810
It's the eternal dilemma for women, isn't it?

131
00:06:47,810 --> 00:06:51,190
Do you have a job or a family?

132
00:06:51,190 --> 00:06:54,520
I never thought of having a career.

133
00:06:54,520 --> 00:06:57,620
I wanted normal happiness, so I got married,

134
00:06:57,620 --> 00:07:01,800
and had a kid, but in the end, I'm in divorce mediation.

135
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:05,410
But I think about what's the best for Azusa,

136
00:07:05,410 --> 00:07:08,280
and I'm going to face my husband head-on.

137
00:07:08,280 --> 00:07:10,420
- I see.
- Same goes for you.

138
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:13,010
Why don't you talk about this with Koichi?

139
00:07:13,010 --> 00:07:18,090
But this is something I should decide for myself.

140
00:07:19,150 --> 00:07:21,150
Mr. Minazuki...

141
00:07:21,150 --> 00:07:25,070
Would you please reconsider the house?

142
00:07:25,070 --> 00:07:28,880
That place is vital to us.

143
00:07:28,880 --> 00:07:30,580
I...

144
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:34,560
want to live there with Saki.

145
00:07:35,560 --> 00:07:37,070
I see...

146
00:07:37,070 --> 00:07:39,670
So she gave up? Going to Paris.

147
00:07:39,670 --> 00:07:42,060
P-Paris?

148
00:07:43,200 --> 00:07:44,880
Saki didn't tell you?

149
00:07:44,880 --> 00:07:47,700
N-No...

150
00:07:49,250 --> 00:07:52,280
Once I'm done with the new book I'm writing,

151
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:56,000
Saki is going to Paris for training.

152
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:59,720
Training? Training would be...

153
00:07:59,720 --> 00:08:01,580
One week?

154
00:08:03,200 --> 00:08:05,370
One month?

155
00:08:08,340 --> 00:08:10,960
Three years.

156
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:12,930
Three years?

157
00:08:12,930 --> 00:08:14,310
Th...

158
00:08:15,110 --> 00:08:16,900
Sorry for coming so late.

159
00:08:16,900 --> 00:08:18,760
It's fine.

160
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:20,510
There's...

161
00:08:20,510 --> 00:08:22,560
something I want to talk to you about.

162
00:08:42,190 --> 00:08:44,510
It's...

163
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,360
What is it?

164
00:08:54,950 --> 00:08:56,480
Well...

165
00:08:57,490 --> 00:08:59,170
Um...

166
00:09:00,170 --> 00:09:03,440
How do I put it?

167
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,400
It's that...

168
00:09:07,740 --> 00:09:09,360
Saki?

169
00:09:34,570 --> 00:09:36,700
<i>I love being an editor.</i>

170
00:09:36,700 --> 00:09:40,090
<i>I got the job after lots of hard work. It means a lot to me.</i>

171
00:09:40,090 --> 00:09:44,190
<i>I'm proud of the work I do. I don't want to quit.</i>

172
00:10:01,650 --> 00:10:04,480
It's been a while. I'm Rina Shiroki.

173
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:07,240
I'm sorry for calling you here so suddenly.

174
00:10:07,240 --> 00:10:10,430
I wanted to talk.

175
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:13,050
Personally,

176
00:10:13,050 --> 00:10:17,350
I think friendships where gender and age don't matter

177
00:10:17,350 --> 00:10:21,040
truly exist.

178
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:23,530
I hope you don't

179
00:10:23,530 --> 00:10:27,380
judge us alongside other people, just because we're the opposite sex.

180
00:10:27,380 --> 00:10:32,610
Takepon and I really aren't doing anything indecent.

181
00:10:33,410 --> 00:10:37,560
I was born in a different generation.

182
00:10:38,110 --> 00:10:40,320
I'm sorry for my old-fashioned views.

183
00:10:40,320 --> 00:10:43,350
He's really a dear friend to me,

184
00:10:44,130 --> 00:10:46,390
but Takepon and I decided

185
00:10:46,390 --> 00:10:49,430
not to see each other anymore.

186
00:10:49,430 --> 00:10:53,570
Take care of him for me, okay?

187
00:10:54,670 --> 00:10:56,520
Bye.

188
00:10:57,130 --> 00:10:58,910
Wait!

189
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:04,510
If you really are just friends...

190
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:11,920
you can keep being Takepon's friend.

191
00:11:11,920 --> 00:11:14,160
Really?

192
00:11:14,160 --> 00:11:16,120
Of course.

193
00:11:20,650 --> 00:11:21,810
Thank you.

194
00:11:21,810 --> 00:11:23,880
Of course.

195
00:11:29,550 --> 00:11:31,220
Mom?

196
00:11:35,650 --> 00:11:39,380
Do you want anything?

197
00:11:39,380 --> 00:11:42,360
Sorry for bothering you.

198
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:46,020
Don't be silly. Of course, I'd come.

199
00:11:47,020 --> 00:11:50,090
Saki, I know this is belated,

200
00:11:50,090 --> 00:11:53,480
but I feel awful about you and Kaede.

201
00:11:53,480 --> 00:11:55,850
I was a selfish mother.

202
00:11:55,850 --> 00:11:57,790
I'm sorry.

203
00:11:57,790 --> 00:12:00,660
Don't worry about that.

204
00:12:02,730 --> 00:12:05,590
The things you felt as a child,

205
00:12:05,590 --> 00:12:08,210
you end up remembering them

206
00:12:08,210 --> 00:12:13,620
when you're an adult, and you'll feel lonely.

207
00:12:13,620 --> 00:12:16,340
It was like that for me too.

208
00:12:16,340 --> 00:12:18,350
When I was a kid,

209
00:12:18,350 --> 00:12:22,050
my mom was busy with the family business.

210
00:12:22,790 --> 00:12:25,630
She was really strict!

211
00:12:26,200 --> 00:12:29,570
She never hugged me.

212
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,690
I wanted to live

213
00:12:32,690 --> 00:12:36,570
a free and comfortable life,

214
00:12:38,060 --> 00:12:40,850
but I also knew I wasn't a good mother.

215
00:12:40,850 --> 00:12:42,410
I...

216
00:12:42,410 --> 00:12:46,840
always had a voice inside telling me that.

217
00:12:47,870 --> 00:12:50,990
I'm sorry for bringing that up.

218
00:12:57,730 --> 00:13:01,450
Is there such a thing as the perfect mother?

219
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:05,760
There's not.

220
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,240
I guess so...

221
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:13,070
You're perfect the way you are.

222
00:13:17,180 --> 00:13:20,670
You... are my mom.

223
00:13:21,580 --> 00:13:24,020
My precious mom.

224
00:13:28,580 --> 00:13:30,690
Thank you!

225
00:13:40,220 --> 00:13:43,050
You're perfect the way you are too, Mommy.

226
00:13:46,090 --> 00:13:47,970
<i>[Jinya]</i>

227
00:13:49,630 --> 00:13:51,600
Pardon me.

228
00:13:51,600 --> 00:13:54,540
- Is there an Obara...
- Welcome!

229
00:13:55,510 --> 00:13:58,350
Oh, it's just you, Koichi.

230
00:14:01,180 --> 00:14:05,470
For 40 years, I prided myself as a JSDF,

231
00:14:05,470 --> 00:14:09,060
and as a medic.

232
00:14:10,240 --> 00:14:15,000
However, because I no longer hold that position,

233
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:18,770
I've come to realize how worthless I am.

234
00:14:18,770 --> 00:14:23,030
Father, I wouldn't call you "worthless".

235
00:14:24,050 --> 00:14:25,720
No,

236
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:28,600
since coming here,

237
00:14:28,600 --> 00:14:31,380
I now see how inept I am.

238
00:14:31,380 --> 00:14:33,550
That's the reality of it all.

239
00:14:34,450 --> 00:14:36,980
Though I don't know if I can,

240
00:14:36,980 --> 00:14:39,940
I must change.

241
00:14:39,940 --> 00:14:42,560
Even if it may be too late,

242
00:14:43,640 --> 00:14:45,540
I'd like to try.

243
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:49,260
Koichi.

244
00:14:50,930 --> 00:14:53,970
- Yes?
- You'll be fine.

245
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:59,410
Protect the person most important to you

246
00:14:59,410 --> 00:15:02,270
as one, "Koichi Obara".

247
00:15:04,200 --> 00:15:05,660
I will.

248
00:15:09,960 --> 00:15:14,140
Hast thou not gone against sincerity?

249
00:15:14,140 --> 00:15:17,420
Hast thou not felt ashamed of thy words and deeds?

250
00:15:17,420 --> 00:15:21,820
Hast thou not lacked vigor?

251
00:15:21,820 --> 00:15:26,530
Hast thou exerted all possible efforts?

252
00:15:26,530 --> 00:15:32,040
Hast thou not become slothful?

253
00:15:34,030 --> 00:15:36,330
<i>[The Others May Live]
(T/N: Motto from the Air Rescue Wing of the JSDF)</i>

254
00:15:41,540 --> 00:15:44,690
"The Others May Live..."

255
00:15:58,790 --> 00:16:00,330
Commanding Officer.

256
00:16:00,330 --> 00:16:01,980
What's wrong?

257
00:16:03,030 --> 00:16:05,000
Um...

258
00:16:05,000 --> 00:16:06,780
What is it?

259
00:16:09,770 --> 00:16:12,130
What's the meaning of this,

260
00:16:13,250 --> 00:16:15,140
Master Sergeant Obara?

261
00:16:17,720 --> 00:16:19,670
Chapitre deux.
<i>(T/N: Chapter two in French) </i>

262
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:21,310
<i>Just learn along.</i>

263
00:16:21,310 --> 00:16:23,720
- "Just learn along."
- <i>Useful greetings.</i>

264
00:16:23,720 --> 00:16:25,000
"Useful greetings."

265
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:26,560
- <i>Hello</i>.
- "Hello."

266
00:16:26,560 --> 00:16:28,000
<i>Bonjour!
(T/N: Hello in French) </i>

267
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,780
- Sounds a bit wrong.
- <i>Good evening.</i>

268
00:16:29,780 --> 00:16:32,180
"Good evening." Good evening?

269
00:16:32,180 --> 00:16:35,640
So this is a baguette.

