00:16:38,620 --> 00:16:40,960
DÃ©licieuse... Sounds wrong.
<i> (T/N: Delicious in French)</i>

271
00:16:40,960 --> 00:16:42,830
Demi-riz...

272
00:16:42,830 --> 00:16:44,550
Wrong again.

273
00:16:45,480 --> 00:16:47,770
Bleu... Wrong.
<i> (T/N: It's still raw)</i>

274
00:16:47,770 --> 00:16:50,730
Demi-riz...
<i>(T/N: Half portion of rice)</i>

275
00:16:54,280 --> 00:16:56,520
Please, allow me!

276
00:16:59,540 --> 00:17:01,530
I shall do that.

277
00:17:06,940 --> 00:17:08,690
- Look.
- Yes?

278
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:15,020
Could you just tell me using words?

279
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:17,970
Tell me your thoughts,

280
00:17:17,970 --> 00:17:20,310
and what you've been thinking,

281
00:17:20,310 --> 00:17:24,320
about family and us.

282
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:31,850
I always kept

283
00:17:31,850 --> 00:17:34,030
a picture of you and Koichi

284
00:17:34,030 --> 00:17:38,500
within the pocket of my uniform.

285
00:17:39,270 --> 00:17:41,250
Not a day went by

286
00:17:41,250 --> 00:17:43,900
when I didn't think of family.

287
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:48,780
However, I didn't take the effort to express this.

288
00:17:48,780 --> 00:17:52,020
That is why I wish to be here with you.

289
00:17:54,110 --> 00:17:56,490
And if you will allow it...

290
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:00,140
I wish to be in your memories

291
00:18:00,140 --> 00:18:02,180
and your heart.

292
00:18:03,300 --> 00:18:07,910
I came here, in hopes that I could leave an impression on you.

293
00:18:10,140 --> 00:18:15,410
Unfortunately, we cannot return to the married couple we used to be.

294
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:20,180
As expected.

295
00:18:21,890 --> 00:18:25,990
But... I don't mind a different sort of relationship.

296
00:18:26,820 --> 00:18:29,600
Nowadays, people live to 100.

297
00:18:29,600 --> 00:18:32,260
We have plenty of time.

298
00:18:32,940 --> 00:18:35,680
Perhaps, we can...

299
00:18:35,680 --> 00:18:39,410
make plenty of memories together from now on.

300
00:19:35,030 --> 00:19:37,550
I'll be in your care.

301
00:20:08,240 --> 00:20:10,350
Welcome back!

302
00:20:10,350 --> 00:20:13,090
W-Why... are you here?

303
00:20:13,090 --> 00:20:14,520
I got paid leave,

304
00:20:14,520 --> 00:20:18,150
and wanted to eat dinner together.

305
00:20:19,540 --> 00:20:21,370
I see.

306
00:20:23,430 --> 00:20:26,930
Actually, I have something I'd like to discuss with you.

307
00:20:27,440 --> 00:20:29,200
Koichi?

308
00:20:30,740 --> 00:20:31,770
What's wrong?

309
00:20:31,770 --> 00:20:34,800
N-N-Nothing.

310
00:20:34,800 --> 00:20:36,340
<i> [Hello = Bonjour; Half portion of rice = Demi riz]</i>

311
00:20:36,340 --> 00:20:40,270
- What's this?
- N-N-Nothing!

312
00:20:40,270 --> 00:20:42,680
You're hiding something, aren't you?

313
00:20:43,780 --> 00:20:49,250
More importantly, I'd love to eat your cooking.

314
00:21:01,120 --> 00:21:03,220
I'm so full.

315
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:09,430
Do you not... need to head home soon?

316
00:21:09,430 --> 00:21:11,810
Can I stay over tonight?

317
00:21:24,050 --> 00:21:25,760
It's been a while

318
00:21:25,760 --> 00:21:30,270
since we've slept together, like this.

319
00:21:43,870 --> 00:21:45,680
Koichi?

320
00:21:49,170 --> 00:21:54,230
This puts me... at ease.

321
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:15,400
Koichi?

322
00:22:43,800 --> 00:22:46,200
<i>[Letter of Resignation]</i>

323
00:22:47,100 --> 00:22:50,100
What is he doing?

324
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,890
Saki!

325
00:23:18,750 --> 00:23:20,760
Why are you here?

326
00:23:22,200 --> 00:23:24,600
Letter of resignation?

327
00:23:27,220 --> 00:23:30,740
- How do you...
- Why would you go do something like that?

328
00:23:36,540 --> 00:23:38,950
It's to be with you.

329
00:23:43,500 --> 00:23:46,400
What do you mean?

330
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:50,200
I will quit my job and accompany you to Paris.

331
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:52,600
How do you know about Paris?

332
00:23:52,600 --> 00:23:54,600
I heard from Mr. Minazuki.

333
00:23:54,600 --> 00:23:57,600
After he finishes his novel,

334
00:23:57,600 --> 00:24:02,400
you will go study in Paris for three years.

335
00:24:03,600 --> 00:24:06,200
I thought we had another chance,

336
00:24:06,200 --> 00:24:09,900
so I can't stand the idea of being apart once more!

337
00:24:09,900 --> 00:24:14,600
I wish to be with you, even if I lose my job as a medic.

338
00:24:14,600 --> 00:24:17,600
I wish to be with you, as one "Koichi Obara"!

339
00:24:17,600 --> 00:24:21,300
Koichi, you said being a medic was everything.

340
00:24:21,300 --> 00:24:24,100
- You absolutely can't quit!
- However...

341
00:24:25,400 --> 00:24:30,000
then we shall be split apart once more!

342
00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:34,800
Being split apart is agonizing,

343
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:38,200
but isn't this job...

344
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:40,800
your pride and joy?

345
00:24:40,800 --> 00:24:45,100
I don't want you to quit as a medic!

346
00:24:46,300 --> 00:24:50,200
If so... is our only option...

347
00:24:51,100 --> 00:24:52,600
to be...

348
00:24:54,800 --> 00:24:57,180
split apart?

349
00:25:00,400 --> 00:25:04,400
I myself, don't know what to do.

350
00:25:04,400 --> 00:25:09,300
That's why I couldn't tell you about Paris.

351
00:25:10,200 --> 00:25:12,600
Even so,

352
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:15,500
don't decide important things by yourself.

353
00:25:15,500 --> 00:25:18,000
From now on, I want us to talk about it together.

354
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:21,600
I want to discuss how we can stay together,

355
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:23,900
again and over again.

356
00:25:24,700 --> 00:25:26,600
Because I...

357
00:25:26,600 --> 00:25:30,400
decided I wouldn't leave your side, no matter what!

358
00:25:33,000 --> 00:25:36,900
I... won't be going to Paris!

359
00:25:38,200 --> 00:25:40,800
I'll continue working hard, right where I am!

360
00:25:40,800 --> 00:25:43,400
I'll be sure to return

361
00:25:43,400 --> 00:25:47,200
to the world of fashion, by my own efforts!

362
00:25:57,500 --> 00:25:59,340
I understand.

363
00:26:01,090 --> 00:26:03,100
I hear you loud and clear.

364
00:26:08,330 --> 00:26:10,410
It was my fault.

365
00:26:14,500 --> 00:26:16,200
My apologies.

366
00:26:19,030 --> 00:26:20,980
I'm truly sorry.

367
00:26:32,800 --> 00:26:36,700
My deepest apologies for the trouble I've caused.

368
00:26:37,810 --> 00:26:42,130
Do you now understand the weight of resignation, Master Sergeant Obara?

369
00:26:43,440 --> 00:26:44,660
Yes

370
00:26:44,660 --> 00:26:47,140
Moving forth, if something ever comes up,

371
00:26:47,800 --> 00:26:50,200
don't keep it all within yourself.

372
00:26:50,200 --> 00:26:53,300
Talk it out with me, your superior officer.

373
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,700
Thank you very much.

374
00:27:15,100 --> 00:27:17,800
I did not submit my resignation.

375
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:19,600
I'm sorry.

376
00:27:21,000 --> 00:27:22,690
I'm glad.

377
00:27:23,740 --> 00:27:27,200
I've also been feeling lost all this while.

378
00:27:27,200 --> 00:27:31,000
That's why... I'm glad that you've made your decision.

379
00:27:36,300 --> 00:27:38,900
Are you really fine with this?

380
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:42,900
About going to Paris.

381
00:27:44,300 --> 00:27:48,200
That's why... I said I'm okay with it.

382
00:27:49,900 --> 00:27:51,600
I...

383
00:27:52,400 --> 00:27:55,000
really want to know how you truly feel.

384
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:59,000
The fact that you're feeling lost

385
00:27:59,000 --> 00:28:02,500
is the reason why you want to leave, correct?

386
00:28:05,790 --> 00:28:08,460
Are you sure you want to give up on your dream?

387
00:28:14,900 --> 00:28:16,800
I...

388
00:28:18,500 --> 00:28:24,000
want to train in Paris, and I want to be with you.

389
00:28:24,000 --> 00:28:26,600
Those are my true feelings,

390
00:28:26,600 --> 00:28:28,300
but...

391
00:28:30,300 --> 00:28:34,000
I will wait for three years.

392
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:38,500
I've been waiting for 37 years to meet my soulmate, that is you.

393
00:28:39,810 --> 00:28:42,790
Three years is not a problem for me.

394
00:28:45,080 --> 00:28:47,550
Between Mito and Tokyo, and Mito and Paris.

395
00:28:47,550 --> 00:28:49,720
Well, the distance apart is different,

396
00:28:49,720 --> 00:28:53,080
but wherever you go,

397
00:28:54,140 --> 00:28:58,040
I'm confident that my feelings will reach you.

398
00:29:00,210 --> 00:29:04,070
The bond between us isn't that weak.

399
00:29:05,300 --> 00:29:07,200
The future...

400
00:29:11,340 --> 00:29:14,190
is for us to paint ourselves.

401
00:29:18,900 --> 00:29:22,500
I will live my life with you.

402
00:29:24,300 --> 00:29:27,500
That's the only happy future that I can see.

403
00:29:35,240 --> 00:29:36,970
Okay.

404
00:29:40,500 --> 00:29:44,600
I am prepared.

405
00:29:45,600 --> 00:29:47,700
I want to go to Paris.

406
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:51,200
And I want to start things over with you.

407
00:29:51,200 --> 00:29:55,200
For these reasons, I will do my best.

408
00:29:59,400 --> 00:30:03,600
That is the Saki Mizuguchi I'm in love with.

409
00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:07,600
I'm sorry for being selfish.

410
00:30:07,600 --> 00:30:09,200
It's okay.

411
00:30:11,400 --> 00:30:13,100
That...

412
00:30:14,340 --> 00:30:17,620
is the shape of our happiness.

413
00:30:19,300 --> 00:30:22,600
Thank you, Koichi.

414
00:30:31,140 --> 00:30:32,900
I...

415
00:30:34,400 --> 00:30:39,100
want to become your wife, once more.

416
00:30:43,230 --> 00:30:44,950
Me too.

417
00:30:45,610 --> 00:30:47,490
I want to...

418
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:52,820
be your husband once more.

419
00:31:01,600 --> 00:31:04,300
Koichi Obara.

420
00:31:04,300 --> 00:31:07,400
Saki Mizuguchi.

421
00:31:07,400 --> 00:31:08,900
Rules.

422
00:31:09,700 --> 00:31:12,200
I guess greeting each other is important.

423
00:31:12,200 --> 00:31:16,200
"Good morning" during the day and "good night" before we sleep. How do you want to say it?

424
00:31:16,200 --> 00:31:18,800
In that case, how about we video call daily?

425
00:31:18,800 --> 00:31:20,400
Video call?

426
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:23,800
We greet each other, "Good morning,"

427
00:31:23,800 --> 00:31:27,200
every day via video call.

428
00:31:27,200 --> 00:31:29,400
That also includes the greeting of "good night".

429
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:31,700
We greet each other with "good night" too.

430
00:31:31,700 --> 00:31:35,400
And also, we only did this once at our wedding.

431
00:31:35,400 --> 00:31:38,400
That is when you... It's nothing. Forget about it.

432
00:31:39,200 --> 00:31:44,000
Ren Minazuki, known as Yamada Sachio,

433
00:31:44,000 --> 00:31:46,600
has handed back the apartment.

434
00:31:46,600 --> 00:31:48,000
You're a savior!

435
00:31:48,000 --> 00:31:50,700
Thank you very much.

436
00:31:53,000 --> 00:31:54,800
"How I wish

437
00:31:54,800 --> 00:31:57,600
I could turn back the clock to last year's Christmas Eve."

438
00:31:57,600 --> 00:32:00,400
Was what I regretteded hundreds of times over,

439
00:32:00,400 --> 00:32:03,800
but I cannot change the past.

440
00:32:03,800 --> 00:32:05,200
Right now, as your best friend,

441
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:08,800
I wish for your happiness from the bottom of my heart.

442
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:10,500
This time too,

443
00:32:10,500 --> 00:32:13,700
I hope you will find happiness with Obara.

444
00:32:13,700 --> 00:32:14,900
Thank you.

445
00:32:14,900 --> 00:32:16,900
Hungry?

446
00:32:16,900 --> 00:32:18,600
Yes...

447
00:32:18,600 --> 00:32:21,400
- I am.
- You are. Okay.

448
00:32:29,190 --> 00:32:31,930
<i>[The End]</i>

449
00:32:35,600 --> 00:32:37,980
It's a wonderful ending.

450
00:32:39,460 --> 00:32:42,780
You've finally completed it.

451
00:32:53,300 --> 00:32:57,600
This pen, I'm returning it to you.

452
00:32:58,600 --> 00:33:01,800
I guess this marks your graduation.

453
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:06,200
I've also returned your apartment. You're going to Paris?

454
00:33:06,200 --> 00:33:08,200
Yes.

455
00:33:08,200 --> 00:33:11,640
Thank you for your guidance all this while.

456
00:33:13,500 --> 00:33:17,500
Thanks to you, I've come up with a great novel.

457
00:33:17,500 --> 00:33:20,900
A romance novelist realizes what true love is

458
00:33:20,900 --> 00:33:24,800
and continues to look forward to his own future works.

459
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:28,400
Me too. As a reader,

460
00:33:28,400 --> 00:33:31,600
I look forward to enjoying your works.

461
00:33:33,300 --> 00:33:35,200
For dumping me,

462
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:38,400
I shall make you regret.

463
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:42,500
Got it, Sensei Yamada Sachio.

464
00:33:43,800 --> 00:33:46,200
Nice shot!

465
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:47,600
Amazing, amazing!

466
00:33:47,600 --> 00:33:50,200
All right, your turn!

467
00:33:53,900 --> 00:33:55,600
Awesome, nice shot!

468
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,300
It flew.

469
00:33:59,260 --> 00:34:00,870
It flew!

470
00:34:05,730 --> 00:34:08,760
It's great to be back home!

471
00:34:08,760 --> 00:34:11,190
Welcome home!

472
00:34:11,190 --> 00:34:14,110
Oh, you were here!

473
00:34:15,290 --> 00:34:17,710
Congratulations on your discharge.

474
00:34:18,330 --> 00:34:22,640
Life spans 100 years. We still have a long way to go.

475
00:34:23,320 --> 00:34:27,350
Will you marry me one more time?

476
00:34:32,740 --> 00:34:35,150
I'm not getting remarried,

477
00:34:35,940 --> 00:34:37,950
but...

478
00:34:37,950 --> 00:34:41,290
I'll accept these flowers.

479
00:34:42,050 --> 00:34:44,270
First off,

480
00:34:44,270 --> 00:34:47,100
let's start by being friends, shall we?

481
00:34:47,940 --> 00:34:52,350
Thanks to you, I feel like I can live a longer life.

482
00:34:59,080 --> 00:35:01,110
You have a vase?

483
00:35:01,110 --> 00:35:02,460
Yes! A vase, right? Yes, yes.

484
00:35:02,460 --> 00:35:04,420
<i>The bond between husband and wife...</i>

485
00:35:04,420 --> 00:35:05,880
<i>surely...</i>

486
00:35:05,880 --> 00:35:08,450
<i>is shaped by the people around them.</i>

487
00:35:13,530 --> 00:35:15,180
<i>Great. Perfect!</i>

488
00:35:15,180 --> 00:35:16,560
- <i>Look over here.
- Okay! Good.</i>

489
00:35:16,560 --> 00:35:19,130
It's good, that's perfect.

490
00:35:19,130 --> 00:35:20,550
This is...

491
00:35:20,550 --> 00:35:22,160
I want more motions.

492
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:24,840
- Okay.
<i> - Are we not done yet?</i>
- Fine.

493
00:35:24,840 --> 00:35:26,470
Looks good.

494
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:45,140
Oh, there she is!

495
00:35:45,140 --> 00:35:47,830
<i>Koichi, can you hear and see me?</i>

496
00:35:47,830 --> 00:35:49,240
<i>I can hear you,</i>

497
00:35:49,240 --> 00:35:52,300
<i>and I can clearly see you too.</i>

498
00:35:52,300 --> 00:35:53,920
Are you off to work?

499
00:35:53,920 --> 00:35:54,980
<i>Y-Yeah.</i>

500
00:35:54,980 --> 00:35:57,130
It's still night time over here.

501
00:35:57,130 --> 00:36:00,350
We're taking a break during a shoot.

502
00:36:00,350 --> 00:36:02,850
<i>Do not overwork yourself</i>

503
00:36:02,850 --> 00:36:05,080
<i>and have your body break down.</i>

504
00:36:05,080 --> 00:36:07,350
Thanks. You too, Koichi.

505
00:36:07,350 --> 00:36:08,910
Oh, um...

506
00:36:08,910 --> 00:36:12,280
S-Saki, you're too beautiful.

507
00:36:12,280 --> 00:36:14,720
<i>You're cute. So...</i>

508
00:36:14,720 --> 00:36:18,600
<i>try not to smile around</i>

509
00:36:18,600 --> 00:36:20,680
<i>- t-too much.</i>
- <i>What are you talking about?</i>

510
00:36:20,680 --> 00:36:22,160
- Understand?
- <i>I'll be fine.</i>

511
00:36:22,160 --> 00:36:23,890
Under...

512
00:36:24,730 --> 00:36:25,990
Y-You sure will.

513
00:36:25,990 --> 00:36:28,250
<i>Saki, is that your husband?</i>

514
00:36:28,250 --> 00:36:30,290
- <i>Hey, Koichi! How are you doing? </i>
- Who are you?

515
00:36:30,290 --> 00:36:31,850
<i> Everything is going well here.</i>

516
00:36:31,850 --> 00:36:32,940
<i>Saki is so wonderful!</i>

517
00:36:32,940 --> 00:36:34,380
Don't touch her!

518
00:36:34,380 --> 00:36:36,280
Get back!

519
00:36:36,280 --> 00:36:38,700
F-F-France person!

520
00:36:38,700 --> 00:36:40,800
Sorry about that.

521
00:36:41,720 --> 00:36:42,910
My apologies,

522
00:36:42,910 --> 00:36:46,140
<i>I got heated.</i>

523
00:36:46,140 --> 00:36:47,800
In that case...

524
00:36:48,930 --> 00:36:50,960
I'll be off.

525
00:36:50,960 --> 00:36:52,880
Have a good day.

526
00:36:54,500 --> 00:36:57,550
You hang up first.

527
00:36:57,550 --> 00:36:59,140
<i>Okay then.</i>

528
00:36:59,140 --> 00:37:00,950
<i>See you.</i>

529
00:37:01,700 --> 00:37:03,380
<i>See you.</i>

530
00:37:05,280 --> 00:37:07,170
She really hung up first.

531
00:37:09,350 --> 00:37:11,330
<i>I'm sure we have</i>

532
00:37:11,330 --> 00:37:16,080
<i>our own befitting way of being a married couple.</i>

533
00:37:27,720 --> 00:37:30,370
It's been a week.

534
00:37:38,470 --> 00:37:40,270
<i>[Koichi Obara and Saki Mizuguchi's Rules]</i>

535
00:37:42,960 --> 00:37:44,900
<i>[Days Until We Submit Our Marriage Registration: 1,038 Days]</i>

536
00:37:47,250 --> 00:37:50,150
Only 1,038 days remain.

537
00:37:50,150 --> 00:37:51,670
<i>[Days Until We Submit Our Marriage Registration: 1,038 Days]</i>

538
00:37:51,670 --> 00:37:53,920
Let's see...

539
